            <title>[LOG4J2-351] [OSGi] wrong Fragment-Host in manifest files</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-351</link>
                <project id="12310790" key="LOG4J2">Log4j 2</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;(From log4j-user mailing list)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Roland wgl@ids.de via logging.apache.org &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hi all!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve noticed that in some manifests the Bundle-Host is defined as following:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Fragment-Host: org.apache.commons.log4j-api;version=...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But I can not find org.apache.commons.log4j-api in any maven repository!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Should it be org.apache.&lt;b&gt;logging&lt;/b&gt;.log4j-api?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Regards&lt;br/&gt;
Roland&lt;/p&gt;</description>
